---

<section class="relative py-24 lg:py-32">
  <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0">
    <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 right-0 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-slate-700/50 to-transparent"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
    <h2 class="animate-fade-in-up text-center text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl">Frequently asked questions</h2>

    <div class="mt-12 space-y-4">
      <details class="group animate-fade-in-up delay-100 glass-card rounded-2xl p-6 cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-semibold text-white/90 [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
          How is changebrief different from Visualping?
          <svg class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-slate-500 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Visualping shows you an image with red pixels where something changed. You have to figure out what it means yourself. changebrief sends the screenshot pair to AI vision and returns a sentence describing exactly what changed — "Price increased from $29 to $39/mo" instead of a red blob.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group animate-fade-in-up delay-200 glass-card rounded-2xl p-6 cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-semibold text-white/90 [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
          How accurate are the summaries?
          <svg class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-slate-500 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">We use state-of-the-art vision AI that understands what's displayed on a web page — prices, buttons, text, layouts. It compares two versions of the same page and describes exactly what changed in plain language. The importance score (1-10) helps you filter noise from signal.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group animate-fade-in-up delay-300 glass-card rounded-2xl p-6 cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-semibold text-white/90 [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
          Can I monitor pages behind a login?
          <svg class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-slate-500 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Yes! You can configure cookies and HTTP headers per URL. This makes it possible to monitor pages that require authentication, such as internal dashboards or customer portals.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group animate-fade-in-up delay-400 glass-card rounded-2xl p-6 cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-semibold text-white/90 [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
          Where is data hosted?
          <svg class="h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-slate-500 transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">All data is stored within the EU. Screenshots are encrypted at rest. We never share data with third parties beyond what's required for the AI analysis.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
